# ── SECRETS — never commit ───────────────────────────────────────────
# identity.json
# Which guards this client uses — reveals who it talks through.
guard_sample.json
# An authority's committed-but-unrevealed random value. Reading it early
# is exactly the advantage commit-and-reveal denies everyone.
srv_pending.json holds this node's private x25519 static key; hs_identity_*
# files are hidden-service private keys (whoever has one can impersonate
# the site). The whole ~/.phinet store is per-machine state, not source.
.phinet/
identity.json
# Which guards this client uses — reveals who it talks through.
guard_sample.json
# An authority's committed-but-unrevealed random value. Reading it early
# is exactly the advantage commit-and-reveal denies everyone.
srv_pending.json
hs_identity_*.json
*.key
*.pem

